<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Positioning Elements</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="main2.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <img src="fall-autumn-red-season.jpg" alt="Image">
    <p class="bottom-left"> Despite the importance of nature in human life, we are spoiling its balance only due to our greediness.
        .</p>
    <p class="centered">  The study of nature is a large, if not the only, part of science. Although humans are part of nature, human activity is often understood as a separate category from other natural phenomena.</p>
  </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>


//////////////////////
main2.css
/////////////////////
.container {
  position: relative;
  width: 400px; /* Set the width of the container as needed */
  height: 300px; /* Set the height of the container as needed */
  border: 1px solid #ccc; /* Optional: Add a border to the container for visualization */
  margin: 50px auto; /* Optional: Center the container on the page */
  padding: 10px; /* Optional: Add some padding to the container */
}

img {
  position: absolute;
  top: 10px;
  right: 10px;
  margin: 0;
  width:100px;
  height:100px;
}

p.bottom-left {
  position: absolute;
  bottom: 15px;
  left: 15px;
  margin: 0;
}

p.centered {
  position: absolute;
  top: 50%;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
  margin: 0;
}


/* Task 4: Fixed Navigation Bar */
header.fixed-header {
  height: 10%;
  width:100%;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
  font-weight: bold;
  background-color: blue;
  position:sticky ;
  top: 0;
  left: 0; /* Ensures the header stays above other elements */
}

.fixed-header ul {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  width: 100%;
}

.fixed-header li {
  cursor: pointer;
}



